html.body: ER_STRESS AUTHORS: LUIS CRISTOBAL MONRAZ GOMEZ, INSTITUTE CURIE; INNA KUPERSTEIN, INSTITUTE CURIE DESCRIPTION: This diagram depicts the activity of the Unfolded Protein Response (UPR) that leads to endoplasmic reticulum stress and further apoptosis. During the Sars-CoV-2 infection, this mechanism is activated in the infected cells of the host.
"mitochondria associated ER membranes" arecontact sites between the ER and mitochondria with high calcium concentrations enabling mitochondrial calcium uptake
